<p><!-- google_ad_section_start --><br />
<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">●</span> <strong>Interview</strong> with two enterprising young Brits, Priya Lakhani of <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.masalamasala.co.uk">Masala Masala</a> and Jamie Murray Wells of <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.glassesdirect.co.uk/">Glasses Direct</a>.  Alex, Jamie and Priya discuss the advantages and disadvantages of being a young entrepreneur, the importance of education, research and how to take calculated, rather than unnecessary risks when starting a business.  Jamie also talks about why Glasses Direct is advertising on TV, mentoring and seeking advice to supplement your own skills.  Priya reveals how she rapidly built Masala Masala into a successful business as the recession kicked in and how speed of execution is vital.<br />
