<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">●</span> <strong>Interview</strong> with Alex Will and Henry Erskine Crum, the founders of Spoonfed, about their motivation behind starting a web business straight from studying at the London School of Economics, building a site, choosing a board, finding angel funding and managing the pressures of a fast growing web business.  Alex, Henry and Alex also discuss the benefits of a business partner, working together as friends and learning from disagreements.  There&#8217;s also an interesting discussion about business models, iPhone apps, plans for growth and a software as a service marketing toolkit called Bullseye developed in conjunction with Spoonfed.<br />
