<p><strong>Show Notes</strong></p>
<p><strong>Summary</strong></p>
<p>Intro:</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 00:00 Alex introduces what to expect in this week&#8217;s episode.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 02:12 Kelly Magowan of <a href="http://www.sixfigures.com.au">Six Figures</a> reviews <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Secrets-Building-Winning-Business-Griffiths/dp/1865089842">Secrets To Building A Winning Business</a> by Andrew Griffiths.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 10.02 Highlights interview with Richard Grosse of <a href="http://www.andrewjamesforwarding.com/">Andrew James Forwarding</a> members of <a href="http://www.alibaba.com/?src=ibdm_d02p0081e02r03">Alibaba.com</a>.  The full interview can be found <a href="http://www.smallbizpod.co.uk/blog/alibaba-podcast/">here</a>.</p>
<p>Features:</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 12:17 <strong>Interview</strong> with <a href="http://www.kevinkellyunlimited.com/">Kevin Kelly</a>, motivational speaker and one of Ireland&#8217;s foremost coaches and authors on entrepreneurship.  Alex and Kevin discuss how entrepreneurs can unlearn fear and how self-awareness is vital for leaders facing the challenges of 2009, as well as focusing on a dream and keeping ego at bay to make sure you are open to learning from anybody, anywhere.  They also explore how to exceed customers&#8217; expectations, the exceptional execution of every day ideas, making friends of customers, constructive paranoia, and building experience, energy, enthusiasm and focus into sales.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 43:20 Do check out the newly launched <a href="http://www.smallbizpod.co.uk/sevens">SmallBizPod Sevens</a> where you can contribute 7 business tips on a topic you know well to raise your profile and help other startups and small business owners.</p>
