<p><strong>Show Notes</strong></p>
<p><strong>Summary</strong></p>
<p>Intro:</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 00:00 Alex introduces what to expect in this week&#8217;s episode.<br />
<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 02:10 Sponsors section featuring Eva Rene of <a href="http://www.alibaba.com/showroom/LEBO_SL.html">LEBO SL</a>, a member of <a href="http://www.alibaba.com/?src=ibdm_d02p0081e02r03">Alibaba.com</a>, on successful exporting.  The full interview can be found <a href="http://www.smallbizpod.co.uk/blog/alibaba-podcast">here</a>.</p>
<p>Features:</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 05:25 <strong>Interview</strong> with Ori Gal, ceo of <a href="http://www.nu-lens.com/">NuLens</a>, on running a startup based around one innovative idea or invention, using R&amp;D to discover other business opportunities, disrupting markets, creating a business infrastructure around innovators and the challenge of IP and patents.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 13:47 <strong>Interview</strong> with Joe Batista, director and chief creatologist at <a href="http://www.hp.com/hpinfo/index.html">Hewlett-Packard</a> on, curiosity, passion and how to dismantle your business to take another look at research, IP and your brand to make new connections and build new business opportunities.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 21:50 <strong>Interview</strong> with Kanwal Singh, managing director of Indian venture capital firm <a href="http://www.helionvc.com/">Helion Ventures</a>, on innovative business models in India, the importance of cultural relevance and the outlook for venture capital in an economic downturn.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 31:04 <strong>Book Review</strong> from John Peden of <a href="http://letsmove.in">LetsMove.In</a> who reviews <a href="http://www.amazon.co.uk/Marketing-Beermat-Chris-West/dp/190521104X">Marketing on a Beermat</a> by Chris West.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 33:20 Comments from Ed Stivala and a response on the postponement of <a href="http://www.accountancyage.com/accountancyage/news/2231204/pbr08-income-shifting-rules">income-shifting</a> in the Pre-Budget Report.</p>
