<p>Features: </p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial">•</span> 04:08 <strong>Interview</strong> with Kaustav Bhattacharya and Gitanjali Banerjee Bhattacharya about their plans for an entrepreneurial train journey through India called the <a href="http://www.jagritiyatra.com">Jagriti Yatra</a> aimed at inspiring and supporting young social change makers in the country. Alex, Kaustav and Gitanjali also talk about the motivation behind the project, social entrepreneurship in Asia, the impact of grass roots entrepreneurial activity in the more remote areas of India, and how to <a href="http://www.jagritiyatra.com/getinvolved/">get involved</a>.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial">•</span> 26.46 <strong>Comments</strong> from <a href="http://www.gaj-it.com/">Gaj</a> about how much he enjoyed the interview with <a href="http://www.smallbizpod.co.uk/2008/05/12/smallbizpod-68-rachel-elnaugh-interview/">Rachel Elnaugh</a>.  Also from <a href="http://www.jonathanyates.biz/index.html">Jonathan Yates</a> about his new book and recent experiences selling his most recent business.</p>
