<p>This week <a href="http://www.smallbizpod.co.uk/podcasts/Sbp59.mp3">SmallBizPod #59</a>, the small business advice podcast, talks to Charlie Bigham of <a href="http://www.bighams.com/">Bigham&#8217;s</a> which makes ready-to-cook meals.  Charlie talks passionately about the importance of food, how he built his business from his kitchen table and how to deal with demanding customers like the large supermarket chains.</p>
<p>Right click <a href="http://www.smallbizpod.co.uk/podcasts/Sbp59.mp3">here</a> to download.</p>
<p><strong>Click on the play button below to listen now</strong></p>
<p>	<a href="http://www.smallbizpod.co.uk/interview-107" rel="nofollow" onclick="poptastic(this.href); return false;"><img src="http://www.smallbizpod.co.uk/wp-content/themes/sbp/images/playarrowsmall.gif" alt="play small business podcast now" /></a></p>
<p>If you&#8217;d like to subscribe free using an RSS feed or better still iTunes, just follow the <a href="http://www.smallbizpod.co.uk/podcast-faq">podcast screencasts</a> to find out how easy it is to make sure you never miss an episode of SmallBizPod.</p>
<p>For those who&#8217;d like to download SmallBizPod or listen to it now, right click on the download link or left click on the grey arrow button above to play now.</p>
<p><strong>Show Notes</strong></p>
<p><strong>Summary</strong></p>
<p>Intro:</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 00:00 Alex on what&#8217;s coming up in the show.<br />
<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 01:04 Thanks to <a href="http://www.sage.co.uk">Sage</a> for sponsoring SmallBizPod.</p>
<p>Features:</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 02:31 <strong>Interview</strong> with Charlie Bigham, founder and managing director of Bigham&#8217;s.  Charlie talks about his passion for food, how his business  was inspired by fresh ingredients and hot pans while travelling and his frustration as a consumer.  Alex and Charlie also discuss how to keep energy and momentum after 11 years in business, how to deal with demanding customers like the supermarket chains, and growing a business from your kitchen table.  The conversation also covers innovation, building a team, funding and making decisions for the long term.</p>
