<p>Features:</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial">•</span> 03:42 <strong>Interview</strong> with Will King, CEO of KMI the makers of <a href="http://www.shave.com">King of Shaves</a>.  Will talks about the early days of redundancy, stumbling on an idea for a unique shaving prep product and the valley of death and debt his business found itself in during the first couple of years of trading.  The conversation also focuses on passion, persistence, common sense and the need for time to build big brands.  Alex and Will also talk about the weakness of juggling too many balls, the need for focus, the challenge of building a great team and what visitors at <a href="http://www.eeda.org.uk/destinationgrowth/1990_2122.asp">Destination Growth 2007</a> will learn from Will&#8217;s talk.</p>
