<p><strong>Show Notes</strong></p>
<p><strong>Summary</strong></p>
<p>Intro:</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 00:00 Alex on what&#8217;s coming up in the show.<br />
<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 0:50 Thanks for your patience during SmallBizPod&#8217;s switch of servers.<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;"><br />
•</span> 01:51 <a href="http://www.podcampuk.com/">Podcamp UK</a> on 1st &amp; 2nd September 2007 in Birmingham &#8211; see you there!<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;"><br />
•</span> 03:01 Thanks to <a href="http://www.abbeyoffices.com/smallbizpod">Abbey Business Centres</a> for sponsoring the <a href="http://www.smallbizpod.co.uk/blog/">SmallBizPod blog</a>.  Check out the special offer on virtual office services for SmallBizPod readers and listeners.</p>
<p>Features:</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 04:39 <strong>Interview</strong> with Jennifer Irvine of <a href="http://www.purepackage.com/">The Pure Package</a> about how she built her successful healthy food delivery business from her own home kitchen, overcoming set-backs including the theft of computers, cancer and assault while she was six months pregnant.  Jen also reveals how she combined market research with PR to kick-start her business. Alex and Jen also talk about growth plans, whether The Pure Package is only for the rich, the value of recognition and small business awards and how her company won best start-up at the <a href="http://www.startupsawards.co.uk">Start-Up Awards</a>.</p>
<p>Comments:</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">• </span>28:13 Martin Dooley on burning the candle at both ends and an idea for an episode on managing your time.<br />
<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">• </span>29:55 Darryl Caldwell on using pay-per-click or online auctions as a good research tool for products.<br />
<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">• </span>29:55 Email comments from Paul Walber in Aberdeen about developing his own business.<br />
<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">• </span>32:19 The latest people to sign up to the <a href="http://www.frappr.com/smallbizpodcommunity">SmallBizPod Frappr map</a> incluidng <a href="http://www.podhandle.com">Karin Hoegh</a> and Leonie Winson.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 34.18 <strong>Music</strong> &#8211; Love Comes First by Techno Squirrels.</p>
