<p>This week <a href="http://www.smallbizpod.co.uk/podcasts/Sbp38.mp3">SmallBizPod #38</a>, the small business podcast, explores business innovation and the mavericks who are delivering extraordinary business success.  In a lively conversation with Polly LaBarre and Bill Taylor, founders of <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/">Fast Company</a> magazine and authors of <a href="http://www.amazon.co.uk/Mavericks-Work-Original-Minds-Business/dp/0007244061">Mavericks at Work</a>, the show explores how out-thinking the opposition, not simply strength and size, is the key to entrepreneurial success.</p>
<p>Right click <a href="http://www.smallbizpod.co.uk/podcasts/Sbp38.mp3">here</a> to download</p>
<p><strong>Click on the play button below to listen now</strong></p>
