<p>This week <a href="http://www.smallbizpod.co.uk/podcasts/Sbp36.mp3">SmallBizPod #36</a>, the small business podcast, includes an interview with one of Britain&#8217;s youngest and most successful entrepreneurs, Adam Hildreth, who left school at 16 with few qualifications to set up his first business and who at the tender age of 21 is worth £5 million and is now CEO of his second start-up <a href="http://www.crispthinking.com/">Crisp Thinking</a>.</p>
