<p><strong>Show Notes</strong></p>
<p><strong>Summary</strong></p>
<p>Intro:</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 00:00 Alex on what&#8217;s coming up in the show.<br />
<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 01:12 A quick plug for an electronica podcast &#8211; <a href="http://www.beatificpodcast.com">Beatific Podcast</a>.<br />
<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 01:28 BJ Cunningham, branding guru and all round good chap who appeared in SmallBizPod #28, offers listeners a free teleconference Q&amp;A on 23 January 2007 on branding and how it can benefit your bottom line.  If you&#8217;re interested sign up at <a href="http://www.brandevolutionworkshop.com/ask">www.brandevolutionworkshop.com/ask</a></p>
<p>Features:</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 02:41 <strong>Interview</strong> with Adam Hildreth, CEO of <a href="http://www.crispthinking.com/">Crisp Thinking</a>.  Adam talks about what inspired him to launch his first business at the age of 16 and how he was involved with the <a href="http://www.young-enterprise.org.uk/">Young Enterprise</a> initiative at school.  He goes on to discuss his first business Dubit, that launched an online payment card for teenagers and consulted on marketing to the teenage market.  As a veteran of the first dotcom bubble in 1999, Adam discusses online business models then and now and how he sees the current Web 2.0 boom.  Alex and Adam also discuss determination and passion in business, the importance of listening and ways to encourage and support young entrepreneurs.</p>
