<p>This week <a href="http://www.smallbizpod.co.uk/podcasts/Sbp33.mp3">SmallBizPod #33</a> focuses on skills shortages and the implications for businesses large and small.  We hear from Jo Ray, managing director of <a href="http://www.sage.co.uk/home.aspx">Sage UK</a> which commissioned some recent research on this topic, as well as the views of the <a href="http://www.iod.com">Institute of Directors</a> and Lawrence Jones, managing director of <a href="http://www.ukfast.net/">UKFast</a> a Manchester-based ISP.  As usual, there&#8217;s also a round up of comments from listeners and the latest from the SmallBizPod <a href="http://www.frappr.com/smallbizpodcommunity">Frappr map</a> community.</p>
