<p>If you&#8217;d like to subscribe free using an RSS feed, download your free aggregator software like <a href="http://ipodder.sourceforge.net/index.php">Juice</a> or <a href="http://www.dopplerradio.net/">Doppler Radio</a> and right click on the orange subscribe button on the top right hand side of this page copying the link into your aggregator. For those who&#8217;d like to download SmallBizPod or listen to it now, click on the link or player above.</p>
<p><strong>Show Notes</strong></p>
<p><strong>Summary</strong></p>
<p>Intro:</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 00:00 Alex introduces the show and highlights the listener voicemail service for audio feedback via Skype at alex-smallbizpod or +44 20 8133 1656.<br />
<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 02:38 Comments from listeners who&#8217;ve put a pin in the <a href="http://www.frappr.com/smallbizpodcommunity">SmallBizPod Frappr</a> map including: John Ireland, Fred, <a href="http://www.myspace.com/in4rmrecords">Carl Barton</a>, <a href="http://TinyWebLink.com/?pid=547227">Derek Telles</a>, Kare, David Fineberg, <a href="http://www.lamia-cross.com/">Lamia Cross</a>, and <a href="http://www.rjtco.co.uk">James Turner</a>.</p>
<p>Features:</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 05.07 <strong>Interview</strong> with Simon Coyle of <a href="http://www.kshocolat.co.uk/">Kschocolat</a>.  Alex and Simon talk about international trade; how to grow your business through exports; the importance of good distributors and importers; how the Kschocolat brand was built; the inspiration behind the brand; market research; small business quality and differentiation; and the key factors that have lead to business success.</p>
<p>Comments:</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 20:46 Comment from Alan Stevens, the <a href="http://www.mediacoach.co.uk/">MediaCoach</a> who also runs a media training podcast.<br />
<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 22.19 Jason King thanks SmallBizPod for the inspiration behind <a href="http://www.OfficeBuffoon.com">OfficeBuffoon.com</a>!<br />
<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 24.34 Paul Worrall comments on some issues around factoring, a business finance <a href="http://www.vendorfinanceservices.net/">concept</a> he&#8217;s developing and his open source software <a href="http://www.joss4biz.interition.net">podcast</a>.<br />
<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 26.42 Feedback from Guy Kingston of the <a href="http://www.myobpod.com/">Mind Your Own Business</a> podcast and business conversations between SmallBizPod listeners.<br />
<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 27.51 Gordon Graham of the <a href="http://orxilinasia.blogspot.com/">Broken Bulbs</a> blogs puts forward some fascinating views on what defines an entrepreneur.</p>
<p>Outro:</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">•</span> 31:42 Alex closes the show and reminds listeners of how to get feedback to SmallBizPod.<br />
